page.title: 13Country Dancing
page.content: On 26th June all Goodwood Area Schools got together and did some country dancing.The Schools Concerned were , Lavant , Tangmere, Boxgrove, North Mundum, West Hampnett, West Dean and Singleton. The dances which we did were Circasian Circle, Big Set , Square dance, Lucky 7 and Badgers wheel. The Country Dancing was held at West Dean. We all had to take our own refreshments. The Girls from Chichester High School put on a dance mime called pinocchio from the story of the wooden puppet . This was the 5th year the country dancing was organised.
